-- Egyptian Court to Rule on Satellite Television Charge Next Month
-- B y   S a l m a   E l   W a r d a n y
-- 2012-09-04T11:21:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-04/egyptian-court-to-rule-on-satellite-television-charge-next-month.html
Egypt’s  Administrative Court 
reserved judgment until Oct. 13 in the case of a satellite
television channel head accused of inciting the president’s
murder, according to a faxed statement from the court today.  Tawfik Okasha, the head of the Al-Faraeen channel, faces
allegations of incitement to kill President Mohamed Mursi and of
publicly insulting him.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Salma El Wardany in Cairo at 
 selwardany@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  